    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 102991,
      "reputation" : 385162,
      "user_id" : 276101,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 67,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/30fe97e726af0ea4ff8b756fbf2e6d15?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "polygenelubricants",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/276101/polygenelubricants"
    },
    "is_accepted" : true,
    "score" : 1237,
    "last_activity_date" : 1275567555,
    "creation_date" : 1275567555,
    "answer_id" : 2965808,
    "question_id" : 2965747,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "<p>Quite a few problems with your code:</p>\n\n<h3>On <code>Arrays.asList</code> returning a fixed-size list</h3>\n\n<p>From the API:</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p><a href=\"http://java.sun.com/javase/6/docs/api/java/util/Arrays.html#asList%28T...%29\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><code>Arrays.asList</code></a>: Returns a <strong>fixed-size list</strong> backed by the specified array.</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>You can't <code>add</code> to it; you can't <code>remove</code> from it. You can't structurally modify the <code>List</code>.</p>\n\n<h3>Fix</h3>\n\n<p>Create a <code>LinkedList</code>, which supports faster <code>remove</code>.</p>\n\n<pre><code>List&lt;String&gt; list = new LinkedList&lt;String&gt;(Arrays.asList(split));\n</code></pre>\n\n<hr>\n\n<h3>On <code>split</code> taking regex</h3>\n\n<p>From the API:</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p><a href=\"http://java.sun.com/javase/6/docs/api/java/lang/String.html#split%28java.lang.String%29\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><code>String.split(String regex)</code></a>: Splits this string around matches of the given <a href=\"http://java.sun.com/javase/6/docs/api/java/util/regex/Pattern.html#sum\" rel=\"noreferrer\">regular expression</a>.</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p><code>|</code> is a regex metacharacter; if you want to split on a literal <code>|</code>, you must escape it to <code>\\|</code>, which as a Java string literal is <code>\"\\\\|\"</code>.</p>\n\n<h3>Fix:</h3>\n\n<pre><code>template.split(\"\\\\|\")\n</code></pre>\n\n<hr>\n\n<h3>On better algorithm</h3>\n\n<p>Instead of calling <code>remove</code> one at a time with random indices, it's better to generate enough random numbers in the range, and then traversing the <code>List</code> once with a <code>listIterator()</code>, calling <code>remove()</code> at appropriate indices. There are questions on stackoverflow on how to generate random but distinct numbers in a given range.</p>\n\n<p>With this, your algorithm would be <code>O(N)</code>.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 146146,
      "reputation" : 41,
      "user_id" : 356422,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/04baf32044c4356408d9c5c2a4040193?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Mayank Gupta",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/356422/mayank-gupta"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 4,
    "last_activity_date" : 1275571840,
    "creation_date" : 1275571840,
    "answer_id" : 2966380,
    "question_id" : 2965747,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "<p>This UnsupportedOperationException comes when you try to perform some operation on collection where its not allowed and in your case, When you call <code>Arrays.asList</code> it does not return a <code>java.util.ArrayList</code>. It returns a <code>java.util.Arrays$ArrayList</code> which is an immutable list. You cannot add to it and you cannot remove from it.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 3007353,
      "reputation" : 159,
      "user_id" : 2551594,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/203b7d3a685bdcb18055354b6ee18c18?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Venkat",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2551594/venkat"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 2,
    "last_activity_date" : 1497300129,
    "last_edit_date" : 1497300129,
    "creation_date" : 1372965757,
    "answer_id" : 17477003,
    "question_id" : 2965747,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>You can't remove, nor can you add to a fixed-size-list of Arrays.</p>\n\n<p><strong>But you can create your sublist from that list.</strong></p>\n\n<p><code>list = list.subList(0, list.size() - (list.size() - count));</code></p>\n\n<pre><code>public static String SelectRandomFromTemplate(String template, int count) {\n   String[] split = template.split(\"\\\\|\");\n   List&lt;String&gt; list = Arrays.asList(split);\n   Random r = new Random();\n   while( list.size() &gt; count ) {\n      list = list.subList(0, list.size() - (list.size() - count));\n   }\n   return StringUtils.join(list, \", \");\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>*Other way is </p>\n\n<pre><code>ArrayList&lt;String&gt; al = new ArrayList&lt;String&gt;(Arrays.asList(template));\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>this will create ArrayList which is not fixed size like Arrays.asList</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 3168724,
      "reputation" : 21481,
      "user_id" : 2678170,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 0,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/m0c0q.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Salim Hamidi",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2678170/salim-hamidi"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 16,
    "last_activity_date" : 1477333792,
    "last_edit_date" : 1477333792,
    "creation_date" : 1378672522,
    "answer_id" : 18688414,
    "question_id" : 2965747,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>I think that replacing:</p>\n\n<pre><code>List&lt;String&gt; list = Arrays.asList(split);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>with</p>\n\n<pre><code>List&lt;String&gt; list = new ArrayList&lt;String&gt;(Arrays.asList(split));\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>resolves the problem.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 2137644,
      "reputation" : 17369,
      "user_id" : 1897010,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/mI4YJ.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Mujammil H Kazi",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1897010/mujammil-h-kazi"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 3,
    "last_activity_date" : 1497300142,
    "last_edit_date" : 1497300142,
    "creation_date" : 1379936156,
    "answer_id" : 18958246,
    "question_id" : 2965747,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Yes, on <code>Arrays.asList</code>, returning a fixed-size list.</p>\n\n<p>Other than using a linked list, simply use <code>addAll</code> method list.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Example:</strong></p>\n\n<pre><code>String idList = \"123,222,333,444\";\n\nList&lt;String&gt; parentRecepeIdList = new ArrayList&lt;String&gt;();\n\nparentRecepeIdList.addAll(Arrays.asList(idList.split(\",\"))); \n\nparentRecepeIdList.add(\"555\");\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1810034,
      "reputation" : 2014,
      "user_id" : 1646298,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 82,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/f4cbd3b26e9904b80405f7b2f27db2c9?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "ZZ 5",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1646298/zz-5"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 4,
    "last_activity_date" : 1497300058,
    "last_edit_date" : 1497300058,
    "creation_date" : 1424135342,
    "answer_id" : 28553071,
    "question_id" : 2965747,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>I've got another solution for that problem:</p>\n\n<pre><code>List&lt;String&gt; list = Arrays.asList(split);\nList&lt;String&gt; newList = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;(list);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>work on <code>newList</code> ;)</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1636164,
      "reputation" : 17453,
      "user_id" : 1509583,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 20,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/FYMpP.png?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Gagandeep Singh",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1509583/gagandeep-singh"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1460693413,
    "creation_date" : 1460693413,
    "answer_id" : 36638114,
    "question_id" : 2965747,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Following is snippet of code from Arrays </p>\n\n<pre><code>public static &lt;T&gt; List&lt;T&gt; asList(T... a) {\n        return new ArrayList&lt;&gt;(a);\n    }\n\n    /**\n     * @serial include\n     */\n    private static class ArrayList&lt;E&gt; extends AbstractList&lt;E&gt;\n        implements RandomAccess, java.io.Serializable\n    {\n        private static final long serialVersionUID = -2764017481108945198L;\n        private final E[] a;\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>so what happens is that when asList method is called then it returns list of its own private static class version which does not override add funcion from AbstractList to store element in array. So by default add method in abstract list throws exception.</p>\n\n<p>So it is not regular array list.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 4779799,
      "reputation" : 2212,
      "user_id" : 3861913,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/uKxic.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Karthik Kompelli",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/3861913/karthik-kompelli"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 4,
    "last_activity_date" : 1542377053,
    "last_edit_date" : 1542377053,
    "creation_date" : 1542376616,
    "answer_id" : 53339278,
    "question_id" : 2965747,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Replace </p>\n\n<pre><code>List&lt;String&gt; list=Arrays.asList(split);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>to</p>\n\n<pre><code>List&lt;String&gt; list = New ArrayList&lt;&gt;();\nlist.addAll(Arrays.asList(split));\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>or</p>\n\n<pre><code>List&lt;String&gt; list = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;(Arrays.asList(split));\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>or</p>\n\n<pre><code>List&lt;String&gt; list = new ArrayList&lt;String&gt;(Arrays.asList(split));\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>or (Better for Remove elements)</p>\n\n<pre><code>List&lt;String&gt; list = new LinkedList&lt;&gt;(Arrays.asList(split));\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 15908780,
      "reputation" : 89,
      "user_id" : 11479225,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-B3s2UQ1BWKM/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/ACHi3rcN5pZ2FhMYZFIDAgo3tAFGafF8Hw/mo/s256-rj/photo.jpg",
      "display_name" : "Roushan Kumar",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/11479225/roushan-kumar"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 2,
    "last_activity_date" : 1558694835,
    "last_edit_date" : 1558694835,
    "creation_date" : 1558693420,
    "answer_id" : 56290730,
    "question_id" : 2965747,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p><code>Arrays.asList()</code>  uses fixed size array internally.<br>\nYou can't dynamically add or remove from this<code>Arrays.asList()</code></p>\n\n<p>Use this </p>\n\n<pre><code>Arraylist&lt;String&gt; narraylist=new ArrayList(Arrays.asList());\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>In <code>narraylist</code> you can easily add or remove items.</p>\n"
  }, {
